As the stadium of the 2002 World Cup in Japan and Korea, this is the place where football fans make pilgrimages to punch cards. There is a small museum on the first floor, which is open until 5 p.m. Samsung Shuiyuan's home court is also here. On March 7, 2018, Shanghai Shenhua went to battle with Samsung Shuiyuan of Korea. More than 3,900 people entered the field that day. More than 1,500 of them were our people. According to the reaction of the villagers and elders in front of the TV, we sang loudly and crushed the home fans. After the enthusiasm, we urged each other to clean up the scene. There was no litter left in the stands. Even the Japanese media praised the expedition.
